 values, and have focused on morals, an approach that—Adams claims—is inadequate for formulating and solving the problem of horrendous evils. She emphasizes instead the fruitfulness of other evaluative categories such as purity and defilement, honor and shame, and aesthetics. If redirected, philosophical reflection on evil can, Adams's book demonstrates, provide a valuable approach not only to theories of God and evil but also to pastoral care.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Mrz 2024) 0aGood and evil. 0aTheodicy. 4aPhilosophy. 4aReligious Studies.  aReligion.  abeing a good person.  abible analysis.  abible studies.  abiblical horrors.  abooks for bible study.  abooks for christians.  abooks for seminary students.  achristian philosophy.  achristian solution to evil.  achristian theology.  acomparative religion.  acomparative religious studies.  acontemporary analytic philosophy.  aethics of belief.  aevil according the bible.  aevil and the god of love.  aevil human nature.  aevil in humanity.  aevil in practice.  aevil people.  aexistence of evil.  afaith in god.  agood and evil.  agood human nature.  agoodness.  ajustify God.  aknowledge of god.  ametaphysics.  anature of good and evil.  aphilosophical debates on evil.  aphilosophical evil.  aphilosophical studies.  aphilosophical theology.  aphilosophical treatise.  aphilosophy of evil.  aphilosophy of good and evil.  aphilosophy of religion.  aproblems of evil.  areligion and philosophy.  areligion studies.  areligious metaphysics.  areligious philosophy.  areligious studies.  athe goodness of god.  athe nature of evil.  athe nature of good.  athe praxis of evil.  athe problem of hell.  atheodicy.  atheological discourse.  atheological studies.  atheology and the pr